.\" termin.al-name: skills
.\" termin.al-usage: skills
.\" termin.al-summary: Open skills content.
.TH SKILLS 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
skills \- Open skills content.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
skills
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Opens the fixed virtual document
.B ~/skills.md
as rendered Markdown in the current pane's inline viewer.
.SH VIEWER
Use j/k or arrows to move, PageUp/b and PageDown/Space to page, g/G to jump, / to search, n/N for matches, and q or Escape to return. Mobile controls provide Escape, movement and Prefix.
.SH FAILURES
Extra arguments are rejected. Missing content produces the stable content-unavailable diagnostic; cancellation opens nothing.
.SH NOTES
The document is read-only. Returning preserves the shell transcript, history and current directory.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ skills
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
tools(1), about(1), open(1)
